ZCZC GE09
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 252300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING A LOW PRESSURE AREA WILL LIE BETWEEN
SCOTLAND AND ICELAND. A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL BE
CENTRED IN MID-ATLANTIC. DURING SATURDAY THE LOW CENTRE
WILL MOV NWARDS WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING
ACROSS THE UK ALTHOUGH A SMALL LOW CENTRE WILL RUN INTO
SW ENGLAND. THIS LOW CENTRE WILL MOV QCKY ACROSS THE UK
TO THE BALTIC LATER SUNDAY AND A TRANSITORY RIDGE OF
HIGH PRESSURE WILL MOV ACROSS THE UK WITH A DEEP LOW
CENTRE IN MID-ATLANTIC. THE DPN LOW PRESSURE AREA 969
WILL MOV TO BAILEY BY MIDDAY MONDAY. THROUGH FRIDAY
EVENING AND SATURDAY WINDS WILL BE WIDELY STRG WITH
OCCASIONAL GALES IN NERN SEA AREAS PERHAPS SEV GALES IN
FAIR ISLE AND POSS GALES LATER IN DOVER AND WIGHT. GALES
ARE EXP IN THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT ON SUNDAY MORNING BUT
OTHERWISE STRG WINDS WILL MOD. STRG WINDS WITH GALES IN
THE N WILL RETURN ON MONDAY
